page.title: 10HUNTINGDON POST NEWS JULY 5.
page.content: An accident on the A604 resulted in a 22 year old man's death. He was driving his new moterbike and was involved in a four vehicle pile up.Earlier this week there has been two other serious crashes on the A6O4 resulting in serious injuries. Television star Rustie Lee host of Game for a laugh show visited the locality on saturday to open a new homefit showroom. Peacemakers at RAF Alconbury and Molesworth have been accused of damage to the fence.The jury have retired to consider their verdict. Burglars caused Â£4,OOO of damage to a local house by spraying paint on carpets and smashing crockery. A further Â£6,OOO cash was also stolen. A 31 year old jogger was fined Â£10 for butting a ten year old school boy who had taunted him.
